                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word Jesus is rubricated</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                  <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                  Decorative designs:
                  <locus target="#1r" facs="003">fols. 1r, </locus> (red and black haräg);
                  <locus target="#1r #6v #89r #89v" facs="003 009 091 092">1r, 6v, 89r, 89v, </locus> (line of alternating black and red dots);
                  <locus target="#8r #9r #11v #13r #17r #22r #55r #56v #58r #70v #79v #82r #82v #84v #87v #89r #89v" facs="010 011 014 015 019 024 057 059 060 073 082 084 085 087 090 091 092">8r, 9r, 11v, 13r, 17r, 22r, 55r, 56v, 58r, 70v, 79v, 82r, 82v, 84v, 87v, 89r, 89v</locus> (multiple full stops)
                  </decoNote>
                </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#i(recto)" facs="001">Fol. i(recto)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    unintelligible note
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#iv(erso) #iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fols. iv(erso), iir(ecto)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    blank by erasure
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of ownership with seal:
                    Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘመምሕር፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ለመምሕሬ፡ ገብረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ፲፱፻፳፬፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ኅዳር፡ ሶስት፡ ቀን።</foreign>
                    Translation: This book belongs to owned by Mämhǝr Gäbrä Ḥǝywät who gifted it to Mämhǝr Gäbrä Iyyäsus on 3 Ḫǝdar, 1924 EC (= 13 Nov., 1931 AD)
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <locus target="#90r" facs="092">Fol. 90r</locus>
                    <desc type="RecordTransaction">
                    Note of transaction of book:
                    Text: <foreign xml:lang="gez">በ</foreign>14፡ 8፡ 96፡ <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዓም፡ እኔ፡ ዲ. ኃይለ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ወንድሙ፡ ይችን፡ የዮሐንስ፡ ወንጌል፡ የራሴ፡ በመሆኑ፡ ለችግሬ፡ ሸጨላቼዋለሁ፡ ለመሸጤ፡ በፊርማዬ፡ አረጋግጣለሁ።</foreign>
                    Translation:
                    [Date:] On Miyazya 14, 1996 (EC = April 22, 2004 AD).
                    [Owner:] I am Deacon Ḫaylä Giyorgis Wändǝmu.
                    [Declaration]: Because this <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1693John">Gospel of John</title> is mine, I sold it to him [an unidentified buyer] [to support] my need and I guarantee the selling with my signature .
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                    <desc>
                    unidentified stamp
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#1r" facs="003"> f. 1r and passim</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of ownership by Wäldä Maryam
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#90v" facs="093">Fol. 90v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    unidentified note in a crude hand
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <locus target="#9 #17 #22 #39 #47 #58 #82 #87" facs="011 019 024 041 049 060 084 089">Fols. 9, 17, 22, 39, 47, 58, 82, 87</locus>
                    <desc>
                    brown yarn sewn into corners to mark the location of the readings for the days of the week as navigation system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    Numbered quires: quires 2–9
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <locus target="#2r #6r #13v #14r #16r" facs="004 008 016 016 018">Fols. 2r, 6r, 13v, 14r, 16r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) words of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e8">
                    <locus target="#4r #7v #8r #17v #19v" facs="006 010 010 020 022">Fols. 4r, 7v, 8r, 17v, 19v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) lines of text are written interlinearly;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e9">
                    <locus target="#17r" facs="019"> f. 17r, col.1, line 4</locus><locus target="#34r" facs="036"> f. 34r, col. 2, line 5</locus><locus target="#40v" facs="043"> f. 40v, col 2, line 11</locus><locus target="#44v" facs="047"> f. 44v, col. 2, line 15</locus><locus target="#56r" facs="058"> f. 56r, col.1, line 2</locus>
                    <locus target="#41r #56v" facs="043 059">41r, 56v, </locus><locus target="#2v" facs="005"> f. 2v, col. 1, line 6</locus><locus target="#3r" facs="005"> f. 3r, col. 2, line 14</locus><locus target="#3v" facs="006"> f. 3v, col. 1, line 15</locus><locus target="#4r" facs="006"> f. 4r, col. 1, line 4</locus>
                    <locus target="#5r" facs="007"> f. 5r, col. 1, line 8</locus><locus target="#5v" facs="008"> f. 5v, col 2, line 17</locus><locus target="#8r" facs="010"> f. 8r, col. 1, line 13</locus>
                    <desc>
                    lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (17r; 34r; 40v; 44v; 56r, etc.), and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (41r, 56v, etc.); and in another case interlinearly with the symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (2v; 3r; 3v; 4r; 5r; 5v, etc.);
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e10">
                    <locus target="#9v #52r #58r #67v" facs="012 054 060 070">Fols. 9v, 52r, 58r, 67v</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) erasure markings are visible;
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e11">
                    <locus target="#1v #2r #2v #3r #3v #4r" facs="004 004 005 005 006 006">Fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 3r, 3v, 4r</locus>
                    <desc>
                    (etc.) text has been removed
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e12">
                    <desc>
                    This intervening scribe uses one other approach to intervention that is fairly unique. A first pass has been made through manuscript and notes made in pencil in the margins indicating changes that need to be made. Then the changes themselves were introduced in black ink at the appropriate place in the folios.
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
                <bindingDesc>
                  <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                    <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards covered with tooled leather over decorative linen patches visible inside the turn-ins on front and back cover.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                      <material key="parchment"/>
                      <material key="wood"/>
                      <material key="leather"/>
                      <material key="textile"/>
                    </decoNote>
                  </binding>
                </bindingDesc>
